article.description: Thomas Jefferson rushed for 141 yards on 25 carries with a touchdown and Delaware beat Towson 20-6 on Saturday.
article.headline: Jefferson's 141 yards and TD helps Delaware over Towson 20-6
article.linkText: Jefferson's 141 yards and TD helps Delaware over Towson 20-6
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Thomas Jefferson rushed for 141 yards on 25 carries with a touchdown and Delaware beat Towson 20-6 on Saturday. Jefferson's 40-yard touchdown run midway through the fourth quarter provided the final margin. Delaware (3-5, 1-4 Colonial) piled up 243 yards on the ground, with Jalen Randolph providing 76 yards on 19 carries and Joe Walker added 35 yards on nine carries. Wide receiver Diante Cherry tossed a 21-yard touchdown pass to Randolph in the second quarter to put the Fightin' Blue Hens up 7-3. Frank Raggo added field goals of 30 and 33 yards. Delaware had four interceptions, with Ryan Torzsa hauling in two. Towson (1-7, 0-5) got a pair of field goals from Aiden O'Neill of 27 and 21 yards. The Tigers were outgained 308-206.
